2008-04-06 06:20:02 Source: PLA Daily, Page 1(Staff Report)(Reporters: Zhan Liqi, Kang Jie) The mining district assignment area of Gold Branch No.8 of the Armed Police is in a remote location deep in the mountains. The natural surroundings are harsh.For the last three years, they have invested more than Rmb600,000 in the mining district assignment area to hook up electricity, install satellite television receivers, build a basketball court and a cultural activity room, as well as installing televisions, chess cases, musical instrument cases, drum kit cases, book cases and other cultural materials.They have also, in accordance with the practical conditions of the mining district assignment, formulated a cultural activity plan and established a group to oversee cultural activities so as to regularly hold cultural activities and enrich the cultural life of officers and troops.